{"type":"message","id":"a5e94fbf","parentId":"fc15350b","timestamp":"2026-04-07T14:47:51.520Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"","textSignature":"{\"v\":1,\"id\":\"msg_07cbc123ed7228870169d5191296ac8196af6733384d5209c5\",\"phase\":\"commentary\"}"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_Gp0MB8cZoHaUYazy2UtkIlPv|fc_07cbc123ed7228870169d51912d31c8196b30c2eed637bb8c7","name":"read","arguments":{"file_path":"/vol1/@apphome/trim.openclaw/data/home/.openclaw/media/inbound/replay_auth_selftest---13943f25-55e3-4b4e-a35d-7c62dedc833d","offset":1,"limit":400},"partialJson":"{\"file_path\":\"/vol1/@apphome/trim.openclaw/data/home/.openclaw/media/inbound/replay_auth_selftest---13943f25-55e3-4b4e-a35d-7c62dedc833d\",\"offset\":1,\"limit\":400}"}],"api":"openai-responses","provider":"openai","model":"gpt-5.4","usage":{"input":50563,"output":82,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":50645,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1775573260853,"responseId":"resp_07cbc123ed7228870169d519110e9c8196a11b698b21bacaac"}}
{"type":"message","id":"c1dba776","parentId":"a5e94fbf","timestamp":"2026-04-07T14:47:51.539Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_Gp0MB8cZoHaUYazy2UtkIlPv|fc_07cbc123ed7228870169d51912d31c8196b30c2eed637bb8c7","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"#!/usr/bin/env python3\n\"\"\"\nReplay authorization self-test for self-owned environments.\n\nThis tool is intentionally defensive: it helps site owners validate whether\nrestricted replay or HLS links are exposed in frontend/API responses or remain\ndirectly accessible when a gate/check endpoint says access should be denied.\n\nTypical checks:\n- Does HTML or JSON expose replay URLs before entitlement is enforced?\n- Can an anonymous client fetch a discovered m3u8/mp4 URL directly?\n- If a gate endpoint denies access for an item, is the media URL still usable?\n\nIt does not embed any real target configuration. Supply only assets you own or\nare explicitly authorized to test.\n\"\"\"\n\nfrom __future__ import annotations\n\nimport argparse\nimport json\nimport re\nimport sys\nimport threading\nimport time\nfrom dataclasses import asdict, dataclass, field\nfrom http.server import BaseHTTPRequestHandler, ThreadingHTTPServer\nfrom pathlib import Path\nfrom typing import Any, Dict, Iterable, List, Optional, Sequence, Tuple\nfrom urllib.parse import urljoin\n\nimport requests\n\n\nDEFAULT_TIMEOUT = 15\nMEDIA_SUFFIXES = (\".m3u8\", \".mp4\", \".flv\", \".mp3\", \".aac\", \".ts\", \".m4s\")\nABSOLUTE_URL_RE = re.compile(r\"https?://[^\\s'\\\"<>]+\", re.IGNORECASE)\nRELATIVE_MEDIA_RE = re.compile(\n    r\"\"\"(?P<q>['\"])(?P<url>(?:/|\\.{1,2}/)[^'\"\\s<>]+?(?:\\.m3u8|\\.mp4|\\.flv|\\.mp3|\\.aac|\\.ts|\\.m4s)(?:\\?[^'\"]*)?)(?P=q)\"\"\",\n    re.IGNORECASE,\n)\n\n\n@dataclass\nclass SourceRecord:\n    source_type: str\n    source_ref: str\n    fetch_context: str\n    status_code: int\n\n\n@dataclass\nclass MediaCandidate:\n    url: str\n    source_type: str\n    source_ref: str\n    fetch_context: str\n    item_id: Optional[str] = None\n    title: Optional[str] = None\n    state: Optional[str] = None\n    field_name: Optional[str] = None\n\n\n@dataclass\nclass URLProbe:\n    status_code: Optional[int] = None\n    final_url: Optional[str] = None\n    accessible: bool = False\n    content_type: Optional[str] = None\n    body_excerpt: Optional[str] = None\n    error: Optional[str] = None\n\n\n@dataclass\nclass GateProbe:\n    url: Optional[str] = None\n    status_code: Optional[int] = None\n    decision: str = \"not_run\"\n    body_excerpt: Optional[str] = None\n    error: Optional[str] = None\n\n\n@dataclass\nclass Finding:\n    url: str\n    item_id: Optional[str]\n    title: Optional[str]\n    discovered_from: str\n    discovered_via: str\n    source_type: str\n    source_fetch_context: str\n    anonymous: URLProbe\n    authenticated: Optional[URLProbe]\n    gate: Optional[GateProbe]\n    child_probe: Optional[URLProbe]\n    risks: List[str] = field(default_factory=list)\n    notes: List[str] = field(default_factory=list)\n\n\ndef normalize_base_url(base_url: Optional[str]) -> Optional[str]:\n    if not base_url:\n        return None\n    return base_url.rstrip(\"/\")\n\n\ndef parse_cookie_header(cookie_header: str) -> Dict[str, str]:\n    cookies: Dict[str, str] = {}\n    for part in cookie_header.split(\";\"):\n        piece = part.strip()\n        if not piece or \"=\" not in piece:\n            continue\n        key, value = piece.split(\"=\", 1)\n        cookies[key.strip()] = value.strip()\n    return cookies\n\n\ndef build_session(\n    *,\n    headers: Sequence[str],\n    cookie_header: Optional[str],\n    timeout: int,\n) -> requests.Session:\n    session = requests.Session()\n    session.headers[\"User-Agent\"] = \"ReplayAuthSelfTest/1.0\"\n    session.headers[\"Accept\"] = \"*/*\"\n    for raw in headers:\n        if \":\" not in raw:\n            raise ValueError(f\"invalid header format: {raw!r}\")\n        key, value = raw.split(\":\", 1)\n        session.headers[key.strip()] = value.strip()\n    if cookie_header:\n        session.cookies.update(parse_cookie_header(cookie_header))\n    session.request = with_default_timeout(session.request, timeout)\n    return session\n\n\ndef with_default_timeout(request_func: Any, timeout: int) -> Any:\n    def wrapped(method: str, url: str, **kwargs: Any) -> requests.Response:\n        kwargs.setdefault(\"timeout\", timeout)\n        kwargs.setdefault(\"allow_redirects\", True)\n        return request_func(method, url, **kwargs)\n\n    return wrapped\n\n\ndef trim_text(text: str, limit: int = 220) -> str:\n    compact = re.sub(r\"\\s+\", \" \", text).strip()\n    return compact[:limit]\n\n\ndef try_json_loads(text: str) -> Optional[Any]:\n    try:\n        return json.loads(text)\n    except json.JSONDecodeError:\n        return None\n\n\ndef dedupe_preserve_order(items: Iterable[str]) -> List[str]:\n    seen: set[str] = set()\n    result: List[str] = []\n    for item in items:\n        if item in seen:\n            continue\n        seen.add(item)\n        result.append(item)\n    return result\n\n\ndef extract_absolute_urls(text: str) -> List[str]:\n    urls = [match.group(0).rstrip(\"',);\") for match in ABSOLUTE_URL_RE.finditer(text)]\n    return dedupe_preserve_order(url for url in urls if is_media_url(url))\n\n\ndef extract_relative_media_urls(text: str, base_url: Optional[str]) -> List[str]:\n    if not base_url:\n        return []\n    urls = [urljoin(base_url + \"/\", match.group(\"url\")) for match in RELATIVE_MEDIA_RE.finditer(text)]\n    return dedupe_preserve_order(url for url in urls if is_media_url(url))\n\n\ndef extract_media_urls_from_text(text: str, base_url: Optional[str]) -> List[str]:\n    urls = extract_absolute_urls(text)\n    urls.extend(extract_relative_media_urls(text, base_url))\n    return dedupe_preserve_order(urls)\n\n\ndef looks_like_media_path(value: str) -> bool:\n    lowered = value.lower()\n    return any(token in lowered for token in MEDIA_SUFFIXES)\n\n\ndef is_media_url(value: str) -> bool:\n    lowered = value.lower()\n    return lowered.startswith((\"http://\", \"https://\")) and looks_like_media_path(lowered)\n\n\ndef normalize_urls_from_value(value: Any, base_url: Optional[str]) -> List[str]:\n    if value is None:\n        return []\n    if isinstance(value, list):\n        urls: List[str] = []\n        for item in value:\n            urls.extend(normalize_urls_from_value(item, base_url))\n        return dedupe_preserve_order(urls)\n    if isinstance(value, dict):\n        urls: List[str] = []\n        for item in value.values():\n            urls.extend(normalize_urls_from_value(item, base_url))\n        return dedupe_preserve_order(urls)\n    if not isinstance(value, str):\n        return []\n\n    stripped = value.strip()\n    parsed = try_json_loads(stripped) if stripped.startswith((\"[\", \"{\")) else None\n    if parsed is not None:\n        return normalize_urls_from_value(parsed, base_url)\n\n    urls = extract_media_urls_from_text(stripped, base_url)\n    if urls:\n        return urls\n\n    if looks_like_media_path(stripped):\n        if stripped.startswith((\"http://\", \"https://\")):\n            return [stripped]\n        if base_url and stripped.startswith((\"/\", \"./\", \"../\")):\n            return [urljoin(base_url + \"/\", stripped)]\n    return []\n\n\ndef discover_media_from_json(\n    obj: Any,\n    *,\n    base_url: Optional[str],\n    source_type: str,\n    source_ref: str,\n    fetch_context: str,\n    path: str = \"$\",\n) -> List[MediaCandidate]:\n    candidates: List[MediaCandidate] = []\n\n    if isinstance(obj, dict):\n        item_id = first_present(obj, (\"id\", \"itemId\", \"contentId\", \"videoId\", \"lessonId\", \"courseId\"))\n        title = first_present(obj, (\"title\", \"name\", \"course\", \"lessonName\"))\n        state = first_present(obj, (\"state\", \"status\"))\n        for key, value in obj.items():\n            normalized_key = key.lower()\n            should_scan = normalized_key in {\n                \"replayurls\",\n                \"replayurl\",\n                \"playurl\",\n                \"playurls\",\n                \"m3u8\",\n                \"m3u8url\",\n                \"url\",\n                \"urls\",\n                \"source\",\n                \"src\",\n                \"video\",\n                \"videos\",\n                \"hls\",\n            }\n            urls = normalize_urls_from_value(value, base_url) if should_scan else []\n            if not urls and isinstance(value, str):\n                urls = extract_media_urls_from_text(value, base_url)\n            for url in urls:\n                candidates.append(\n                    MediaCandidate(\n                        url=url,\n                        source_type=source_type,\n                        source_ref=source_ref,\n                        fetch_context=fetch_context,\n                        item_id=str(item_id) if item_id is not None else None,\n                        title=str(title) if title is not None else None,\n                        state=str(state) if state is not None else None,\n                        field_name=key,\n                    )\n                )\n            if should_scan and not isinstance(value, (dict, list)):\n                continue\n            if should_scan and isinstance(value, list) and all(not isinstance(item, (dict, list)) for item in value):\n                continue\n            candidates.extend(\n                discover_media_from_json(\n                    value,\n                    base_url=base_url,\n                    source_type=source_type,\n                    source_ref=source_ref,\n                    fetch_context=fetch_context,\n                    path=f\"{path}.{key}\",\n                )\n            )\n        return dedupe_candidates(candidates)\n\n    if isinstance(obj, list):\n        for index, item in enumerate(obj):\n            candidates.extend(\n                discover_media_from_json(\n                    item,\n                    base_url=base_url,\n                    source_type=source_type,\n                    source_ref=source_ref,\n                    fetch_context=fetch_context,\n                    path=f\"{path}[{index}]\",\n                )\n            )\n        return dedupe_candidates(candidates)\n\n    if isinstance(obj, str):\n        return [\n            MediaCandidate(\n                url=url,\n                source_type=source_type,\n                source_ref=source_ref,\n                fetch_context=fetch_context,\n            )\n            for url in extract_media_urls_from_text(obj, base_url)\n        ]\n\n    return []\n\n\ndef discover_media_from_text(\n    text: str,\n    *,\n    base_url: Optional[str],\n    source_type: str,\n    source_ref: str,\n    fetch_context: str,\n) -> List[MediaCandidate]:\n    parsed = try_json_loads(text)\n    if parsed is not None:\n        return discover_media_from_json(\n            parsed,\n            base_url=base_url,\n            source_type=source_type,\n            source_ref=source_ref,\n            fetch_context=fetch_context,\n        )\n    return [\n        MediaCandidate(\n            url=url,\n            source_type=source_type,\n            source_ref=source_ref,\n            fetch_context=fetch_context,\n        )\n        for url in extract_media_urls_from_text(text, base_url)\n    ]\n\n\ndef dedupe_candidates(candidates: Iterable[MediaCandidate]) -> List[MediaCandidate]:\n    seen: set[Tuple[str, str, str, Optional[str], Optional[str]]] = set()\n    result: List[MediaCandidate] = []\n    for candidate in candidates:\n        key = (\n            candidate.url,\n            candidate.source_type,\n            candidate.source_ref,\n            candidate.item_id,\n            candidate.field_name,\n        )\n        if key in seen:\n            continue\n        seen.add(key)\n        result.append(candidate)\n    return result\n\n\ndef first_present(obj: Dict[str, Any], keys: Sequence[str]) -> Optional[Any]:\n    for key in keys:\n        if key in obj and obj[key] not in (None, \"\"):\n            return obj[key]\n    return None\n\n\ndef fetch_source(\n    *,\n    url: str,\n    anon_session: requests.Session,\n    auth_session: Optional[requests.Session],\n    source_type: str,\n) -> Tuple[Optional[str], Optional[SourceRecord]]:\n    try:\n        response = anon_session.get(url)\n        response.raise_for_status()\n        return response.text, SourceRecord(\n            source_type=source_type,\n            source_ref=url,\n            fetch_context=\"anonymous\",\n            status_code=response.status_code,\n        )\n    except Exception:\n        if not auth_session:\n            return None, None\n    if auth_session:\n        try:\n            response = auth_session.get(url)\n            response.raise_for_status()\n            return response.text, SourceRecord(\n                source_type=source_type,\n                source_ref=url,\n\n[521 more lines in file. Use offset=401 to continue.]"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1775573271534}}
{"type":"message","id":"9529cfc7","parentId":"c1dba776","timestamp":"2026-04-07T14:48:02.505Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_iw9bVLRUhpVVOoKIYLXNXCay|fc_07cbc123ed7228870169d5191da7c08196b8f0791ad3794795","name":"read","arguments":{"file_path":"/vol1/@apphome/trim.openclaw/data/home/.openclaw/media/inbound/replay_auth_selftest---13943f25-55e3-4b4e-a35d-7c62dedc833d","offset":401,"limit":400},"partialJson":"{\"file_path\":\"/vol1/@apphome/trim.openclaw/data/home/.openclaw/media/inbound/replay_auth_selftest---13943f25-55e3-4b4e-a35d-7c62dedc833d\",\"offset\":401,\"limit\":400}"}],"api":"openai-responses","provider":"openai","model":"gpt-5.4","usage":{"input":53384,"output":75,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":53459,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1775573271541,"responseId":"resp_07cbc123ed7228870169d5191ba4e081968acaa3347ada5281"}}
{"type":"message","id":"66999a56","parentId":"9529cfc7","timestamp":"2026-04-07T14:48:02.518Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_iw9bVLRUhpVVOoKIYLXNXCay|fc_07cbc123ed7228870169d5191da7c08196b8f0791ad3794795","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"                fetch_context=\"authenticated\",\n                status_code=response.status_code,\n            )\n        except Exception:\n            return None, None\n    return None, None\n\n\ndef load_file_source(path: Path) -> Tuple[str, SourceRecord]:\n    text = path.read_text(encoding=\"utf-8\")\n    return text, SourceRecord(\n        source_type=\"file\",\n        source_ref=str(path),\n        fetch_context=\"local\",\n        status_code=200,\n    )\n\n\ndef looks_like_login_page(text: str) -> bool:\n    lowered = text.lower()\n    markers = (\"login\", \"sign in\", \"signin\", \"unauthorized\", \"forbidden\", \"access denied\")\n    return any(marker in lowered for marker in markers)\n\n\ndef probe_url(session: requests.Session, url: str) -> URLProbe:\n    headers: Dict[str, str] = {}\n    if not url.lower().endswith(\".m3u8\"):\n        headers[\"Range\"] = \"bytes=0-1023\"\n    try:\n        response = session.get(url, headers=headers)\n        content_type = response.headers.get(\"Content-Type\")\n        content_type_lower = (content_type or \"\").lower()\n        text_excerpt: Optional[str] = None\n        accessible = response.status_code in (200, 206)\n        if url.lower().endswith(\".m3u8\"):\n            text_excerpt = response.text[:1000]\n            accessible = accessible and \"#EXTM3U\" in response.text\n        elif \"text/html\" in content_type_lower:\n            text_excerpt = trim_text(response.text)\n            accessible = accessible and not looks_like_login_page(response.text)\n        elif \"text\" in content_type_lower:\n            text_excerpt = trim_text(response.text)\n        return URLProbe(\n            status_code=response.status_code,\n            final_url=response.url,\n            accessible=accessible,\n            content_type=content_type,\n            body_excerpt=text_excerpt,\n        )\n    except Exception as exc:\n        return URLProbe(error=str(exc))\n\n\ndef first_playlist_child(playlist_text: str, base_url: str) -> Optional[str]:\n    for raw_line in playlist_text.splitlines():\n        line = raw_line.strip()\n        if not line or line.startswith(\"#\"):\n            continue\n        return urljoin(base_url, line)\n    return None\n\n\ndef heuristic_gate_decision(\n    *,\n    body: str,\n    allow_regex: Optional[str],\n    deny_regex: Optional[str],\n) -> str:\n    if allow_regex and re.search(allow_regex, body, re.IGNORECASE):\n        return \"allow\"\n    if deny_regex and re.search(deny_regex, body, re.IGNORECASE):\n        return \"deny\"\n\n    parsed = try_json_loads(body)\n    if isinstance(parsed, dict):\n        if \"fee\" in parsed:\n            return \"allow\" if str(parsed[\"fee\"]) == \"0\" else \"deny\"\n        if \"allowed\" in parsed:\n            return \"allow\" if bool(parsed[\"allowed\"]) else \"deny\"\n        if \"success\" in parsed and isinstance(parsed[\"success\"], bool):\n            return \"allow\" if parsed[\"success\"] else \"deny\"\n        for key in (\"code\", \"status\"):\n            value = parsed.get(key)\n            if value in (0, \"0\", \"ok\", \"OK\", \"allow\", \"ALLOW\", \"success\", \"SUCCESS\"):\n                return \"allow\"\n            if value in (401, 403, \"401\", \"403\", \"deny\", \"DENY\", \"forbidden\", \"FORBIDDEN\"):\n                return \"deny\"\n\n    lowered = body.lower()\n    if any(token in lowered for token in (\"forbidden\", \"denied\", \"unauthorized\", \"not allowed\")):\n        return \"deny\"\n    if any(token in lowered for token in (\"allowed\", \"authorized\", \"granted\")):\n        return \"allow\"\n    return \"unknown\"\n\n\ndef probe_gate(\n    *,\n    item_id: Optional[str],\n    session: Optional[requests.Session],\n    gate_url_template: Optional[str],\n    username: Optional[str],\n    allow_regex: Optional[str],\n    deny_regex: Optional[str],\n) -> Optional[GateProbe]:\n    if not item_id or not session or not gate_url_template:\n        return None\n    gate_url = gate_url_template.format(id=item_id, item_id=item_id, username=username or \"\")\n    try:\n        response = session.get(gate_url)\n        body = response.text\n        return GateProbe(\n            url=gate_url,\n            status_code=response.status_code,\n            decision=heuristic_gate_decision(body=body, allow_regex=allow_regex, deny_regex=deny_regex),\n            body_excerpt=trim_text(body),\n        )\n    except Exception as exc:\n        return GateProbe(url=gate_url, error=str(exc), decision=\"error\")\n\n\ndef analyze_candidate(\n    candidate: MediaCandidate,\n    *,\n    anon_session: requests.Session,\n    auth_session: Optional[requests.Session],\n    gate_session: Optional[requests.Session],\n    gate_url_template: Optional[str],\n    username: Optional[str],\n    gate_allow_regex: Optional[str],\n    gate_deny_regex: Optional[str],\n    probe_child: bool,\n) -> Finding:\n    anonymous = probe_url(anon_session, candidate.url)\n    authenticated = probe_url(auth_session, candidate.url) if auth_session else None\n    gate = probe_gate(\n        item_id=candidate.item_id,\n        session=gate_session,\n        gate_url_template=gate_url_template,\n        username=username,\n        allow_regex=gate_allow_regex,\n        deny_regex=gate_deny_regex,\n    )\n\n    child_probe: Optional[URLProbe] = None\n    if probe_child and anonymous.accessible and candidate.url.lower().endswith(\".m3u8\") and anonymous.body_excerpt:\n        child_url = first_playlist_child(anonymous.body_excerpt, candidate.url)\n        if child_url:\n            child_probe = probe_url(anon_session, child_url)\n\n    risks: List[str] = []\n    notes: List[str] = []\n\n    if candidate.source_type in (\"page\", \"api\", \"file\"):\n        risks.append(\"frontend_or_api_exposes_media_url\")\n        notes.append(f\"Media URL was visible in {candidate.source_type}: {candidate.source_ref}\")\n\n    if anonymous.accessible:\n        risks.append(\"anonymous_media_access\")\n        notes.append(\"Anonymous session could fetch the media URL directly.\")\n\n    if gate and gate.decision == \"deny\" and anonymous.accessible:\n        risks.append(\"gate_denied_but_media_still_accessible\")\n        notes.append(\"Gate denied access, but the media layer still served the URL.\")\n\n    if auth_session and authenticated and authenticated.accessible and not anonymous.accessible:\n        notes.append(\"Media URL looked reachable only after authenticated requests.\")\n\n    if gate and gate.decision == \"unknown\":\n        notes.append(\"Gate result could not be classified automatically; add --gate-allow-regex or --gate-deny-regex.\")\n\n    return Finding(\n        url=candidate.url,\n        item_id=candidate.item_id,\n        title=candidate.title,\n        discovered_from=candidate.source_ref,\n        discovered_via=candidate.field_name or \"text-scan\",\n        source_type=candidate.source_type,\n        source_fetch_context=candidate.fetch_context,\n        anonymous=anonymous,\n        authenticated=authenticated,\n        gate=gate,\n        child_probe=child_probe,\n        risks=dedupe_preserve_order(risks),\n        notes=notes,\n    )\n\n\ndef collect_candidates(\n    *,\n    page_urls: Sequence[str],\n    api_urls: Sequence[str],\n    files: Sequence[Path],\n    direct_urls: Sequence[str],\n    anon_session: requests.Session,\n    auth_session: Optional[requests.Session],\n    file_base_url: Optional[str],\n) -> Tuple[List[MediaCandidate], List[SourceRecord]]:\n    candidates: List[MediaCandidate] = []\n    sources: List[SourceRecord] = []\n\n    for url in page_urls:\n        body, record = fetch_source(url=url, anon_session=anon_session, auth_session=auth_session, source_type=\"page\")\n        if body is None or record is None:\n            continue\n        sources.append(record)\n        candidates.extend(\n            discover_media_from_text(\n                body,\n                base_url=url,\n                source_type=\"page\",\n                source_ref=url,\n                fetch_context=record.fetch_context,\n            )\n        )\n\n    for url in api_urls:\n        body, record = fetch_source(url=url, anon_session=anon_session, auth_session=auth_session, source_type=\"api\")\n        if body is None or record is None:\n            continue\n        sources.append(record)\n        candidates.extend(\n            discover_media_from_text(\n                body,\n                base_url=url,\n                source_type=\"api\",\n                source_ref=url,\n                fetch_context=record.fetch_context,\n            )\n        )\n\n    for path in files:\n        body, record = load_file_source(path)\n        sources.append(record)\n        candidates.extend(\n            discover_media_from_text(\n                body,\n                base_url=file_base_url,\n                source_type=\"file\",\n                source_ref=str(path),\n                fetch_context=record.fetch_context,\n            )\n        )\n\n    for url in direct_urls:\n        candidates.append(\n            MediaCandidate(\n                url=url,\n                source_type=\"direct\",\n                source_ref=url,\n                fetch_context=\"manual\",\n            )\n        )\n\n    return dedupe_candidates(candidates), sources\n\n\ndef run_scan(args: argparse.Namespace) -> Dict[str, Any]:\n    anon_session = build_session(headers=args.anon_header, cookie_header=args.anon_cookie, timeout=args.timeout)\n    auth_session = None\n    if args.auth_header or args.auth_cookie:\n        auth_session = build_session(headers=args.auth_header, cookie_header=args.auth_cookie, timeout=args.timeout)\n    gate_session = auth_session if args.gate_use_auth and auth_session else anon_session\n\n    candidates, sources = collect_candidates(\n        page_urls=args.page_url,\n        api_urls=args.api_url,\n        files=[Path(path) for path in args.sample_file],\n        direct_urls=args.candidate_url,\n        anon_session=anon_session,\n        auth_session=auth_session,\n        file_base_url=normalize_base_url(args.file_base_url),\n    )\n\n    findings = [\n        analyze_candidate(\n            candidate,\n            anon_session=anon_session,\n            auth_session=auth_session,\n            gate_session=gate_session,\n            gate_url_template=args.gate_url_template,\n            username=args.username,\n            gate_allow_regex=args.gate_allow_regex,\n            gate_deny_regex=args.gate_deny_regex,\n            probe_child=args.probe_child,\n        )\n        for candidate in candidates\n    ]\n\n    summary: Dict[str, int] = {\n        \"sources_loaded\": len(sources),\n        \"media_candidates\": len(candidates),\n        \"findings\": len(findings),\n    }\n    for finding in findings:\n        for risk in finding.risks:\n            summary[risk] = summary.get(risk, 0) + 1\n\n    return {\n        \"generated_at\": int(time.time()),\n        \"mode\": \"defensive-self-test\",\n        \"inputs\": {\n            \"page_url\": list(args.page_url),\n            \"api_url\": list(args.api_url),\n            \"sample_file\": list(args.sample_file),\n            \"candidate_url\": list(args.candidate_url),\n            \"gate_url_template\": args.gate_url_template,\n            \"gate_use_auth\": args.gate_use_auth,\n        },\n        \"sources\": [asdict(source) for source in sources],\n        \"summary\": summary,\n        \"findings\": [asdict(finding) for finding in findings],\n    }\n\n\nclass MockReplayHandler(BaseHTTPRequestHandler):\n    server_version = \"ReplayAuthSelfTestMock/1.0\"\n\n    def _send(self, status: int, body: bytes, content_type: str) -> None:\n        self.send_response(status)\n        self.send_header(\"Content-Type\", content_type)\n        self.send_header(\"Content-Length\", str(len(body)))\n        self.end_headers()\n        if self.command != \"HEAD\":\n            self.wfile.write(body)\n\n    def do_GET(self) -> None:  # noqa: N802\n        port = self.server.server_address[1]\n        open_playlist = f\"http://127.0.0.1:{port}/media/open/playlist.m3u8\"\n        protected_playlist = f\"http://127.0.0.1:{port}/media/protected/playlist.m3u8\"\n\n        if self.path == \"/schedule\":\n            payload = {\n                \"items\": [\n                    {\"id\": 42, \"title\": \"Open replay exposed in source\", \"state\": 2, \"replayUrls\": open_playlist},\n                    {\"id\": 43, \"title\": \"Protected replay\", \"state\": 2, \"replayUrls\": protected_playlist},\n                ]\n            }\n            body = (\n                \"<html><body><script>window.__DATA__=\"\n                + json.dumps(payload, ensure_ascii=False)\n                + \";</script></body></html>\"\n            ).encode(\"utf-8\")\n            return self._send(200, body, \"text/html; charset=utf-8\")\n\n        if self.path == \"/api/replays\":\n            body = json.dumps(\n                {\n                    \"data\": [\n                        {\"id\": 42, \"title\": \"Open replay exposed in source\", \"state\": 2, \"replayUrls\": [open_playlist]},\n                        {\"id\": 43, \"title\": \"Protected replay\", \"state\": 2, \"replayUrls\": [protected_playlist]},\n                    ]\n                },\n                ensure_ascii=False,\n            ).encode(\"utf-8\")\n            return self._send(200, body, \"application/json; charset=utf-8\")\n\n        if self.path == \"/gate/42\":\n            body = json.dumps({\"fee\": 1, \"message\": \"denied\"}).encode(\"utf-8\")\n            return self._send(200, body, \"application/json; charset=utf-8\")\n\n        if self.path == \"/gate/43\":\n            body = json.dumps({\"fee\": 0, \"message\": \"allowed\"}).encode(\"utf-8\")\n            return self._send(200, body, \"application/json; charset=utf-8\")\n\n        if self.path == \"/media/open/playlist.m3u8\":\n            body = b\"#EXTM3U\\n#EXTINF:5,\\nsegment.ts\\n\"\n            return self._send(200, body, \"application/vnd.apple.mpegurl\")\n\n        if self.path == \"/media/open/segment.ts\":\n            return self._send(200, b\"OPEN_MEDIA_SEGMENT\", \"video/mp2t\")\n\n        if self.path == \"/media/protected/playlist.m3u8\":\n            if self.headers.get(\"X-Test-Auth\") == \"ok\":\n                body = b\"#EXTM3U\\n#EXTINF:5,\\nsegment.ts\\n\"\n                return self._send(200, body, \"application/vnd.apple.mpegurl\")\n            return self._send(403, b'{\"error\":\"forbidden\"}', \"application/json; charset=utf-8\")\n\n        if self.path == \"/media/protected/segment.ts\":\n            if self.headers.get(\"X-Test-Auth\") == \"ok\":\n                return self._send(200, b\"PROTECTED_MEDIA_SEGMENT\", \"video/mp2t\")\n            return self._send(403, b\"forbidden\", \"text/plain; charset=utf-8\")\n\n        return self._send(404, b\"not found\", \"text/plain; charset=utf-8\")\n\n    def log_message(self, format: str, *args: Any) -> None:  # noqa: A003\n        return\n\n\ndef run_self_test(timeout: int) -> int:\n    server = ThreadingHTTPServer((\"127.0.0.1\", 0), MockReplayHandler)\n    thread = threading.Thread(target=server.serve_forever, daemon=True)\n    thread.start()\n    try:\n        port = server.server_address[1]\n        args = argparse.Namespace(\n            page_url=[f\"http://127.0.0.1:{port}/schedule\"],\n            api_url=[f\"http://127.0.0.1:{port}/api/replays\"],\n            sample_file=[],\n            candidate_url=[],\n\n[121 more lines in file. Use offset=801 to continue.]"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1775573282513}}
{"type":"message","id":"b4793342","parentId":"66999a56","timestamp":"2026-04-07T14:48:12.479Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_psX5tRtSrhKjWMfZ3zQ0UePU|fc_07cbc123ed7228870169d519288a6081968ae6ddfe097f373b","name":"read","arguments":{"file_path":"/vol1/@apphome/trim.openclaw/data/home/.openclaw/media/inbound/replay_auth_selftest---13943f25-55e3-4b4e-a35d-7c62dedc833d","offset":801,"limit":250},"partialJson":"{\"file_path\":\"/vol1/@apphome/trim.openclaw/data/home/.openclaw/media/inbound/replay_auth_selftest---13943f25-55e3-4b4e-a35d-7c62dedc833d\",\"offset\":801,\"limit\":250}"}],"api":"openai-responses","provider":"openai","model":"gpt-5.4","usage":{"input":56817,"output":75,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":56892,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1775573282519,"responseId":"resp_07cbc123ed7228870169d51924c59481969a6097b25ed451ae"}}
{"type":"message","id":"d53ecfec","parentId":"b4793342","timestamp":"2026-04-07T14:48:12.492Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_psX5tRtSrhKjWMfZ3zQ0UePU|fc_07cbc123ed7228870169d519288a6081968ae6ddfe097f373b","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"            anon_header=[],\n            anon_cookie=None,\n            auth_header=[\"X-Test-Auth: ok\"],\n            auth_cookie=None,\n            gate_url_template=f\"http://127.0.0.1:{port}/gate/{{id}}\",\n            gate_use_auth=False,\n            gate_allow_regex=None,\n            gate_deny_regex=None,\n            username=None,\n            file_base_url=None,\n            probe_child=True,\n            timeout=timeout,\n        )\n        report = run_scan(args)\n        findings = report[\"findings\"]\n\n        def has_risk(url_fragment: str, risk_name: str) -> bool:\n            return any(url_fragment in finding[\"url\"] and risk_name in finding[\"risks\"] for finding in findings)\n\n        if not has_risk(\"/media/open/playlist.m3u8\", \"anonymous_media_access\"):\n            print(\"[self-test] expected anonymous access finding for open media\", file=sys.stderr)\n            return 1\n        if not has_risk(\"/media/open/playlist.m3u8\", \"gate_denied_but_media_still_accessible\"):\n            print(\"[self-test] expected gate/media mismatch finding for open media\", file=sys.stderr)\n            return 1\n        protected_findings = [finding for finding in findings if \"/media/protected/playlist.m3u8\" in finding[\"url\"]]\n        if not protected_findings:\n            print(\"[self-test] expected protected media finding\", file=sys.stderr)\n            return 1\n        if any(\"anonymous_media_access\" in finding[\"risks\"] for finding in protected_findings):\n            print(\"[self-test] protected media should not be anonymously accessible\", file=sys.stderr)\n            return 1\n        print(json.dumps(report, ensure_ascii=False, indent=2))\n        print(\"[self-test] passed\")\n        return 0\n    finally:\n        server.shutdown()\n        thread.join(timeout=1)\n\n\ndef build_parser() -> argparse.ArgumentParser:\n    parser = argparse.ArgumentParser(\n        description=\"Replay authorization self-test for self-owned environments.\"\n    )\n    parser.add_argument(\"--page-url\", action=\"append\", default=[], help=\"HTML page to scan for replay/media URLs.\")\n    parser.add_argument(\"--api-url\", action=\"append\", default=[], help=\"JSON API endpoint to scan recursively.\")\n    parser.add_argument(\n        \"--sample-file\",\n        action=\"append\",\n        default=[],\n        help=\"Local HTML/JSON response sample to scan. Repeatable.\",\n    )\n    parser.add_argument(\n        \"--candidate-url\",\n        action=\"append\",\n        default=[],\n        help=\"Known replay/media URL to probe directly. Repeatable.\",\n    )\n    parser.add_argument(\n        \"--anon-header\",\n        action=\"append\",\n        default=[],\n        help=\"Header applied to anonymous discovery/probing requests. Format: 'Key: Value'.\",\n    )\n    parser.add_argument(\"--anon-cookie\", help=\"Cookie header value for anonymous context, if needed.\", default=None)\n    parser.add_argument(\n        \"--auth-header\",\n        action=\"append\",\n        default=[],\n        help=\"Header applied to authenticated requests. Format: 'Key: Value'.\",\n    )\n    parser.add_argument(\"--auth-cookie\", help=\"Cookie header value for authenticated requests.\", default=None)\n    parser.add_argument(\n        \"--gate-url-template\",\n        help=\"Optional gate/check endpoint, e.g. 'https://self.test/gate/{id}'. Supports {id}, {item_id}, {username}.\",\n        default=None,\n    )\n    parser.add_argument(\"--gate-use-auth\", action=\"store_true\", help=\"Call the gate endpoint with authenticated context.\")\n    parser.add_argument(\"--gate-allow-regex\", default=None, help=\"Regex that means the gate allows access.\")\n    parser.add_argument(\"--gate-deny-regex\", default=None, help=\"Regex that means the gate denies access.\")\n    parser.add_argument(\"--username\", default=None, help=\"Optional username for gate URL templating.\")\n    parser.add_argument(\n        \"--file-base-url\",\n        default=None,\n        help=\"Base URL used to resolve relative media paths found in local sample files.\",\n    )\n    parser.add_argument(\"--probe-child\", action=\"store_true\", help=\"If the URL is m3u8, also probe the first child URI.\")\n    parser.add_argument(\"--timeout\", type=int, default=DEFAULT_TIMEOUT, help=\"Per-request timeout in seconds.\")\n    parser.add_argument(\"--output\", default=None, help=\"Write the JSON report to this path.\")\n    parser.add_argument(\"--self-test\", action=\"store_true\", help=\"Run the built-in mock verification and exit.\")\n    return parser\n\n\ndef main() -> int:\n    if hasattr(sys.stdout, \"reconfigure\"):\n        sys.stdout.reconfigure(encoding=\"utf-8\")\n    parser = build_parser()\n    args = parser.parse_args()\n\n    if args.self_test:\n        return run_self_test(args.timeout)\n\n    if not (args.page_url or args.api_url or args.sample_file or args.candidate_url):\n        parser.error(\"provide at least one source via --page-url, --api-url, --sample-file, or --candidate-url\")\n\n    try:\n        report = run_scan(args)\n    except Exception as exc:\n        print(f\"[!] {exc}\", file=sys.stderr)\n        return 1\n\n    rendered = json.dumps(report, ensure_ascii=False, indent=2)\n    if args.output:\n        Path(args.output).write_text(rendered, encoding=\"utf-8\")\n    print(rendered)\n    return 0\n\n\nif __name__ == \"__main__\":\n    raise SystemExit(main())\n"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1775573292487}}
{"type":"message","id":"9079418d","parentId":"d53ecfec","timestamp":"2026-04-07T14:48:44.013Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"[[reply_to_current]] 读完了。这个附件其实是一个 **Python 自测脚本**，文件内容是清晰可读的，不是加密二进制。\n\n## 一句话结论\n这是一个：\n\n> **用于自有环境的 replay / 回放授权自测工具**\n\n它的作用是帮站点所有者验证：\n\n- 页面或 API 是否**提前暴露了回放媒体链接**\n- 当 gate/check 接口判定“无权访问”时，媒体 URL 是否依然**可直接匿名访问**\n- m3u8 / mp4 / flv 这类资源是否存在**前端泄露 + 媒体层未拦截**的问题\n\n它是**偏防御/自测**用途，不是攻击脚本。\n\n---\n\n# 这份脚本在做什么\n\n## 它会扫描这些来源\n支持从下面几类输入里发现媒体链接：\n\n- `--page-url`：扫描 HTML 页面\n- `--api-url`：扫描 JSON API\n- `--sample-file`：扫描本地 HTML/JSON 样本\n- `--candidate-url`：直接给已知媒体链接做探测\n\n## 它会识别哪些媒体\n会抓这些后缀：\n\n- `.m3u8`\n- `.mp4`\n- `.flv`\n- `.mp3`\n- `.aac`\n- `.ts`\n- `.m4s`\n\n还支持：\n- HTML/JS 里直接出现的绝对 URL\n- 相对路径媒体 URL\n- JSON 里嵌套字段里的链接\n\n---\n\n# 它的核心检测逻辑\n\n## 1）先发现媒体链接\n会从页面/API/文件里找这些字段附近的 URL：\n\n- `replayUrls`\n- `replayUrl`\n- `playurl`\n- `playurls`\n- `m3u8`\n- `m3u8url`\n- `url`\n- `urls`\n- `source`\n- `src`\n- `video`\n- `videos`\n- `hls`\n\n---\n\n## 2）再分别探测匿名访问 / 登录访问\n对每个候选媒体 URL：\n\n- 用匿名 session 探测\n- 如果提供了认证头/cookie，再用认证 session 探测\n\n判断依据包括：\n- HTTP 状态码\n- Content-Type\n- m3u8 是否包含 `#EXTM3U`\n- 返回 HTML 时是否像登录页/拒绝页\n\n---\n\n## 3）可选再探测 gate/check 接口\n如果你传了：\n\n```bash\n--gate-url-template\n```\n\n它会按 item id 去请求 gate 接口，再把 gate 的结论和媒体实际可访问性对比。\n\n比如：\n- gate 说 deny\n- 但媒体 URL 仍然 200 可用\n\n那它会报一个非常关键的风险：\n\n```text\ngate_denied_but_media_still_accessible\n```\n\n---\n\n## 4）如果是 m3u8，还能继续测第一层子分片\n开了：\n\n```bash\n--probe-child\n```\n\n它会从 m3u8 里取第一条非注释 URI，继续探测子资源是否可访问。\n\n---\n\n# 它会输出哪些风险\n我看到脚本会标记的核心风险包括：\n\n## `frontend_or_api_exposes_media_url`\n前端页面或 API 直接把媒体 URL 暴露出来了。\n\n## `anonymous_media_access`\n匿名用户可以直接访问媒体 URL。\n\n## `gate_denied_but_media_still_accessible`\ngate 接口明明拒绝，但媒体层仍然在放。\n\n这个风险最有价值，因为它说明：\n- 业务鉴权和媒体鉴权脱节\n- 前端/接口泄露的链接能被直接复用\n\n---\n\n# 脚本自带了一个内置 self-test\n它自己起了个本地 mock 服务，模拟两种情况：\n\n## 开放媒体\n- gate 返回 denied\n- 但 m3u8 还能匿名访问\n\n脚本期望把这个识别出来。\n\n## 受保护媒体\n- 没认证时 403\n- 带 `X-Test-Auth: ok` 后可访问\n\n脚本也会验证这类情况不会误报匿名可访问。\n\n也就是说，这脚本本身写得还算规整，不是随便拼的。\n\n---\n\n# 这份脚本适合拿来做什么\n如果你要把它用于**自有站点/自测环境**，它挺适合做：\n\n- 回放授权自检\n- HLS/MP4 暴露检查\n- gate 与媒体层是否一致的验证\n- 接口/页面是否泄露真实播放 URL 的检查\n\n---\n\n# 这份脚本的使用方式\n最典型的调用会像这样：\n\n## 扫页面\n```bash\npython3 replay_auth_selftest.py \\\n  --page-url 'https://example.test/course/123'\n```\n\n## 扫 API\n```bash\npython3 replay_auth_selftest.py \\\n  --api-url 'https://example.test/api/replays'\n```\n\n## 带 gate 检查\n```bash\npython3 replay_auth_selftest.py \\\n  --api-url 'https://example.test/api/replays' \\\n  --gate-url-template 'https://example.test/gate/{id}'\n```\n\n## 带认证态\n```bash\npython3 replay_auth_selftest.py \\\n  --api-url 'https://example.test/api/replays' \\\n  --auth-cookie 'session=xxxx' \\\n  --probe-child\n```\n\n## 跑内置自测\n```bash\npython3 replay_auth_selftest.py --self-test\n```\n\n---\n\n# 我的判断\n这份附件的性质是：\n\n- **不是 exploit**\n- **不是恶意样本**\n- **不是混淆 payload**\n- **是一个偏蓝队 / 自测 / 授权验证工具**\n\n---\n\n如果你愿意，我下一步可以继续帮你做两种事里的一个：\n\n1. **把这个脚本整理成中文说明版**\n2. **结合你刚才那个视频回放/播放鉴权场景，告诉你怎么把这个脚本套进去测**\n\n你回我一个数字就行。","textSignature":"{\"v\":1,\"id\":\"msg_07cbc123ed7228870169d5193112d48196b7f15107c7c81ebf\",\"phase\":\"final_answer\"}"}],"api":"openai-responses","provider":"openai","model":"gpt-5.4","usage":{"input":58030,"output":1346,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":59376,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1775573292494,"responseId":"resp_07cbc123ed7228870169d5192edb6c81968da49816cfbea056"}}
